      "author": "goryugocast",
      "description": "## 0.1.7\n\nFixes a critical regression in 0.1.5 and addresses bot lint scan issues.\n\n### Fixed\n- **Critical**: All commands failed with `undefined is not an object (evaluating 'this.plugins')` on both desktop and mobile in 0.1.5. Caused by lint refactor extracting Obsidian internal methods (`getPluginById`, `setHotkeys`, `posAtCoords`, etc.) and calling them without their receiver, losing `this` binding. Restored proper method invocation.\n- iOS first-tap suppression after debug Notice: `Notice` creation during `pointerdown` is now deferred to a microtask so WebKit doesn't suppress the subsequent `click`.\n\n### Lint / Bot Compliance\n- Resolved obsidian-releases bot findings: `no-base-to-string`, `require-await` (4×), `no-manual-html-headings` (2×).\n- Fixed `package.json` lint script: `eslint \"src/**/*.ts\"` (quoted) so `npm run lint` actually checks `src/main.ts` (previously `**` was eaten by `/bin/sh`).\n- Settings panel headings now use `Setting().setHeading()` per Obsidian style guide.\n\n### Notes for upgraders from 0.1.5\n- This is a strict bug-fix release. No behavioral changes beyond restoring 0.1.4's working state.\n- 0.1.6 was an interim version that did not pass bot scan and is superseded by 0.1.7.\n",
